text: This movie was originally based off Eminem's life. It begins with the boxer rising to the top, like Eminem did in the early 2000's. Then while the boxer is rewarded for his hard work, something bad happens at a public appearance and he loses custody of his daughter, and is suspended for a year. Eminem lost one of his best friends in 2005 and he took a 4 year break from rapping. The boxer has to do everything to get his daughter back and regain his heavyweight title. Eminem had to go to rehab after serious drug problems and then, 2 years later was at his peak. The two stories are very similar

text: My thoughts on the movie (WARNING:SPOILERS) The movie wasn't as good as I thought it'd be. Every 5 minutes you had someone going on a rampage and tearing shit up. Also they brought up many things in the movie that they didn't really put too much detail or effort into it. Overall the movie was quite great, but he losses to a no name fighter and never redeems that loss and comes back to win against the guy who was involved in killing his wife. Also I was thinking he'd eventually tell Will he was the reason his wife died after they found out what happened with Hoppy's family. The movie could have also been resolved if he never started that brawl in the lobby, which was never mentioned again afterwards. Eminem had a good soundtrack that made the movie better. The movies overall plot was pretty predictable. The split decision loss also made no sense considering Hope was caught with a low blow and his opponent got a point deducted without a warning, so he would have loss the fight if I recall correctly. And the movies whole name revolves around Billy Hope switching his stance once in the fight just to catch his opponent with an uppercut in his southpaw stance and didn't finish the fight. I'd give this movie a 6/10.

text: What I learned from this movie is that sometimes you are your worst enemy! He destroyed himself, he destroyed his family! His anger got his wife killed and his actions became his habits and his habits became his character! Sometimes its best to be the bigger person and walk away! He protected his wife by fighting the other guy, but what did he get out of it? I loved this movie because the message was so deep! It was sad but he knew he had to fight! He was feeling pain but what he really needed to understand was that, he needed to be strong for his daughter also because she too was feeling hurt and anger! He finally woke up and realized that his biggest fear was himself, and he had to control his anger because all it was doing was killing him! This movie is just a big thumbs up!

text: There is no denying that the physical transformation Jake Gyllenhaal went through to play boxer Billy Hope was amazing. He is almost unrecognisable as the same man who played Louis Bloom in Nightcrawler . Sadly this film cannot hold a candle to that one . Having grown up watching and enjoying the Rocky films you would have thought i would have embraced this film but i didn't and that's simply because the boxing scenes were so terrible. With Rocky you expect the exaggerated punches and cartoon like action but with this i wanted more realistic sporting action. Sadly it almost bordered on comedic. The best bits of this film were definitely all outside the ring and even those were packed full of head shaking cliches.  This is film that promised so much but failed to pack any significant punches. 5 out of 10

text: This is one of those movies that can trick you into thinking they are good, but if you look at it closely and analyze it, it is a cliched mess. What worked in the movie are performances, especially Gyllenhaal who was great in his role and supporting cast does terrific job although the daughter overacts but it is fine. It is a well directed film and solid entry to the boxing genre. Everything else failed in my opinion. Plot is way too contrived and derivative, come on Rocky 3 anyone, it gets way too heavy for its own good, it is filled with drama that i did not care for or connected emotionally with the characters, looks forced and shallow, there are huge plot holes, it is uninspiring, formulaic, predictable, overlong and it is simply tedious film. 2/5

text: I might get a lot of hate for saying this, but imo it was kind of a disappointing movie. I was expecting more from it. It reminded me just too much of the Rocky movies, I mean yea I love Rocky movies but I was expecting this movie to be different. But it turned out to be just like most movies about boxers, with the same kind of clich√© storyline about a burnt out boxer going through a rough patch in his life, then finding a new trainer, then the boxer starts to work his way up again, then he wins the most important title match in a 12 round match in a really close fight and then a happy ending...nothing surprising or new. Don't get me wrong, I still liked this movie, but to me it wasn't anything special. Good acting from Jake and Rachel looked smoking hot as usual, other than that it was just an "okay" movie.
